>like those outlined in this submission </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we have been able to make sustained progress.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Overall </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BU</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> now employs 309 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> academ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ics to 342 male academics, another positive sign that the ratio of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Professors will improve in the coming years as more junior academics’ careers progress.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BU has learnt important l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">essons from this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">experience, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> we believe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> can be applied to othe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r instituti</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ons starting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">low base</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> numbers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of female academics.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ssues </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and challenges that we have encountered </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">extend beyond STEM subjects </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">directly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> applicable to many different subject areas. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Interestingly, not all </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">challenges are rest</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ricted to women either.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There are no simple answers to the questions raised by this inquiry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, rather many different issues </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n in academia encounter, which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">when </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">combined compound the problem of under</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> representation of wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n in STEM.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">attempted to provide an exhaustive sum</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mary of all the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> issues </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in this submission</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (which will vary by institution and according to different women’s experience). Instead we have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">noted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the problems which were frequently raised in discussions with women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in aca</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">demia </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BU.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times