11pt">key </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">developments in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> such</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> rapidly changing research areas and institutions.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> other</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> careers it can be much easier to take </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">maternity leave </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and time</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> off to care for children, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for women in academia there is never a good time to be out of their field.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In practical terms, statutory rates of maternity pay in academia are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">relatively</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> low, meaning women taking time off to h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ave children face fina</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ncial penal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ties</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. They also often feel that they have to c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ontinue </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">working</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> while off campus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, since it is impossible to bring in a direct replacement in their area of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">specialism and expertise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> This can create a very frustrating compromise situation, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">where women typically continue working </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">while on maternity leave, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">still feel that the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ir careers are set back by taking time off, as they inevitably publish less and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">risk </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ss</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> key developments in their field.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in academia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ind the retur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n to work and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the year immediately following maternity leave</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> particularly challenging. They may not receive any</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> additional administrative support or r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eduction in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">teaching </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">workload, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">but still have to catch up on research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> work afte</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r a year’s absence while</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">f course, continuing to care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">children.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As one academic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> succinctly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> puts it</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">‘The bottom-line is that academia does not currently</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">make it easy in any way for women to retain their research ca</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">reers when they have children.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Academia is highly competitive, and it is very difficult for women to keep their careers on a par with men </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">if they wish to have children.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">It's easier not to bother trying’.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As well as issues with caring for children, balancing academic careers with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">partne</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’ careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also cause difficulties for wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n in academia.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> partner</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">non-academic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be prioritised, being more likely to provide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">permanent rather than </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">fixed term contract and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">re stability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If the ‘non-academic partner’ moves to take up another role it can often be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an area where the woman cannot find a suitable academic position.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">relationship</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">other acade</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s may not be immune to this. A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lthough such a relationship could be t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hought to work well in terms of balancing a career, a woman with a partner who is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> more senior academic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">level to herself </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">may find herself disadvantaged if they have to relocate to another university</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The situation essentially becomes a self-fulfilling </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">prophecy.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nother</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> fundamental issue affecting retention of women in STEM subjects is the poor availability of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">permanent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> contracts in academia. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Generally, it takes slightly longer in academia to reach the experience level appropriate for permanent posts, and unfortunately this tends to coincide with the time at which people are seeking to purchase houses and/or start a family. Consequently many wo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">men </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">leave academia, or never enter it in the first place, in favour of more stable careers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Due in part to these </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">challenges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, culturally</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> there is a shortage of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> role models in many universities,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> with few (or no) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women visibly holding senior academic positions. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> can in turn affect the confidence and ambition of other wo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">men as well as affecting the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">availability of female mentors.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A lack of women in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> senior positions can also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">affect recruitment and lead to a soli</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">difying of the status</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> quo, as senior male academics (consciously or subconsciously)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recruit colleagues and successors in their own image</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In addition </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to recruitment panels potentially tending to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recruit in their own likeness, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has shown that ther</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e can often be an ‘un</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">conscious bias’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> against women.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">For example, in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> terms of applications for jobs and p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">romotion, when CVs are judged blindly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women fare better on average, but when names are included, men</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> have the advantage</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Some women also describe </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">encountering ‘anti-role models’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (one </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">academic described</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> them as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ‘Margaret Thatcher</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’ characters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> who after rising through the ranks</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">themselves </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">do not necessarily promote or encourage other women, and do not see the n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eed for a wider gender balance </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">other</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> tha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n themselves as a lone figure at the top.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">One academic writes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“There are also women that use their single or childless status to their advant</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">age.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">or example one candidate seeking a Chair stating that ‘Well, I’m gay – so you don’t have to worry about me g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">oing off to have children’. Not strictly true, but she got the post.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.14</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Female academics</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> have also reported experiencing harassment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> more frequently</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an underlying prejudice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on account of their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gender, which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">obvious</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ly has a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> negative</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">effect</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> morale and the retention of female academics.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Some women recount</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> being viewed as automatically less capable than male colleagues, less interested in promotion, and potentially distracted from their careers by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">decisions to have children.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.15</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">One academi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">c writes that while no-one would openly admit to ho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lding or expressing such views,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Equally no-one</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">wants to speak out about the daily issues they have encountered in the fear of having their name blackened or career slighted. Academia is a small world, dep</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">endent on your reputation and personal networks, so a small amount of negativity can have a huge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> impact on your personal career”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.16</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">At a cul</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tural level many women also encounter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ‘macho practices’ within male-dominated disc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">iplines such as STEM, sometimes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">having to be highly assertive to ensure they receive credit for their work, such as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> inclusion of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> their names on research papers co-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">authored</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> with male colleagues.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">One academic comments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">‘Quite simply, many women do not feel this is a modus operandi they can</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> tolerate, let alone flourish in’.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:15.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Question 2: When women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? What are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different employment sectors?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that BU</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> consulted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for this inquiry were obviously all still within academia, and many</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> still</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> within STEM subjects. They were therefore unable to comment personally on reasons for leaving academia, but many reported friends and colleagues’ experiences. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Anecdotally, it appears that most women who leave </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM subjects </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">do so </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in favour of working in business.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This is partly attributed to companies in the private sector being able to offer more appealing maternity leave and childcare benefits than universities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, along with more competitive salaries.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Some women also move into management schemes for large private companies after completing PhDs in STEM subjects, which not only draws them away from academic careers, but can also be count</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">erintuitive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as these are of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ten careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> they could have followed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">after </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an undergraduate degree, without needing a Doctorate to qualify.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:15.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Question 3: What should universities and the higher education sector do to retain women graduates and PhD students in academic careers? Are there e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">xamples of good practice?</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:15.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Preparing this submission has been an interesting exercise for BU, and we are extremely grateful to everyone who gave up their time to put forward comments and experiences. We strongly believe in the value of diversity and the p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ositive effect that it has on our ability to be creative and innovative. We also feel very strongly that it is completely unacceptable for anyone to feel harassed or subject to underlying prejudice. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As a result of this submission, we will be recommending</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a review of BU’s maternity policy and the support we provide to colleagues on their return to work. We will also recommend that BU explores possible actions to bring about a cultural change in attitude towards women in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">academia, including how we can bette</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r celebrate those who successfully combine their career with family commitments.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">However, it is important to note that BU academics were recounting their experiences from across their entire career span, and that significant progress on supporting women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in academia has been made over the last few years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">niversity-wide Women’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Academic Network </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(WAN) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has been established, with support from the highest level being provided as a key institutional priority.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Such networks can serve multi-faceted purposes; r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">aising the profile of existing women academics across the University, serving as networking forums allowing women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in academia to meet regularly (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">including </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">via social events),</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and arranging </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">events</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> with high-profile, inspirational speakers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">At </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BU</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Networ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">k</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> also provides a means by which the University can identify the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> important issues affecting wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n academic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s, crowd-source potential remedies, and maintain a direct dialogue with women over whether </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">introduced </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">measur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">es are having a positive effect</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> would highly recommend the establishment of such a network</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to all universities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">preferably </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">built into the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">institution’s formal structures.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> institution we have also signe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d up to the Athena SWAN</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Charter -</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a national initiative which recognises and celebrates good pract</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ice in maintaining and promoting wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n academics in STEM subjects. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Along with many other universities we are also taking part in th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e Athena Swan Awards, which are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> proving a rigorous, external</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ly verified means of monitoring and celebrating our progress in this area.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We strongly recommend that all u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">niversities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sign up to the Athena S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">WAN </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">initiative, and would suggest </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">holding a week of events to promote the initiative internally.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BU</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> has also intr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">oduced an Associate Professor grade, a post in which holders are provi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ded with considerable advice and development opportunities to support them in pro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gressing to full Professorships within three to five years.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are currently eight wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n Associate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Professors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which gives us confidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">further </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">significantly increase the number of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Professors at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BU</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> over the next few years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There are also other general measures </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> women consulted at B</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">U believe that universities across the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> could </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">take to improve the retention of women in STEM.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> For example:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities should ensure they have policies on mentoring women in STEM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> built into their structures</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> more women in STEM reach senior positions, they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> be encouraged to act as role m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">odel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s through mentoring schemes -</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> giving inspirati</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on and encouragement to mentees -</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">thus </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ensuring that the process becomes a positive cycle.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">University </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">HR</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> departments should also ensure they have ‘safe’ procedures for women to anonymously report any instances of sexism or harassment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">they face in the course of their work.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities could offer particular incentives aimed at encouraging woman with PhD</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s or Post-Doctoral experience to return to academia after pursuing other careers, for example fellowships especially tailored to this and advertised as such.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As discussed above, one of the biggest practical problems for women’s progression in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">HE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is the dif</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ficulty in taking adequate maternity leave without falling behind in their research.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Addressing this problem would go a long way </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">improving retention </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in academic careers for women graduates.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Many women report that friends and contemporaries working in th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e private sector receive longer periods of paid maternity leave, and in addition are less likely to have demands made </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of them whilst on leave. It is important that all universities regularly review their maternity leave packages and support arrangements fo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r when </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> return to work. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities could</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ensure </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women have reduced duties i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n their first year </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">after maternity leave, thereby making the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">transition back to work easier</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and improving their productivity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Women could choose to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">focus either on rese</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">arch or teaching in their first year back.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Some women report on r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eturning they found themselves </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">being used to plug holes in the teaching schedule, rather than going back to their research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Regardless of the ethical issues involved, this means the women c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">oncerned find themselves with an increased rather than reduced work burden, as they have to write new lectures and teaching plans.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Another issue for women combining academic careers in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> STEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">with family responsibilities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is the long hours such careers often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">involve. Universities should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ensure that women are able to work the most flexible, child-friendly hours possible.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ensure that there are adequate nursery and playgroup places to cater for the children of academics either on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or within easy distance of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> campus.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> hosting academic events such as conferences and seminars</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> universities or other groups</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ould also ensure that childcare provision is provided for attendees.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">who</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> combine a successful academic career with bringing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> up children should</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> be publically celebrated within universities. T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">his could </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be combine</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d with mentoring programmes so </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">visible mothers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in STEM can offer confidential help and support to colleagues.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Although many universities have been making progress </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on tackling the under-representation of women in STEM, there is clearly more that can be done, and given </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">they face a potential drain of talent from academia, universities need to be more proactive in combatting this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">both for the sake of equality, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for their own institutional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">effectiveness.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:15.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Question 4: What role should the Government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">initial </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">onus to provide more sustainable, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">permanent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">contr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">acts for academics is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">universities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. However</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, Government also has an important role in securing these </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recognising the importance of protecting research a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nd development funding for STEM, both through the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> UK Treasury and from international sources, particularly the European Com</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mission. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">One suggestion </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is that the Government should set national targets for the number of men in s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">enior roles in Higher Education.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> A target of, for example, no more than 60% of roles in university leadership </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">teams being held by men by 2020</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> wo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uld give </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a strong message, and c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uld also be a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">less contentious approach than</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> introduction of quotas for women.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">At a national level, the Government could also set targets </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to ensure that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> all funding bodies m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">aking decisions about awards </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">have an equal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">number of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">men and women on the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ir decision-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">making panels.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The next Research Excellence</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Framework process, scheduled for 2018, could also monitor gender equality </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">amongst researchers, and potentially make the availability of schemes such as mentoring of women in STEM,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and participation in national </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">initiatives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> such as the Athena SWAN</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Awards, conditions of funding.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Government can also play a role in working with Universities UK and other scientific bodies to promote success stories of women in STEM nationally, ensuring </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Ministers frequently celebrate particular case studies and best practice.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:15.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Conclusion</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">inquiry by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Science and Technology Select Committee into the issue of women in STEM subjects is to be welcomed as an initial step </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">towards evaluating the extent o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">f the problem, and concentrating minds natio</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nally on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">possible solutions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We hope</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that the Government will serious</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ly consider any collective</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recommendations made, and that the Committee will continue to return to the issue and monitor progress.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Bournemouth</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> University</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> would be delighted to give oral evidence on these issues as part of the Select Committee inquiry, if required.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/features/why-are-there-so-few-female-vice-chancellors/2006576.article</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> Dr. Heather Savigny, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">Senior Lecturer in Politics at Bournemouth University has written a paper, ‘Women Know your Limits; Cultural Sexism in Academia’ currently under peer review prior to publication, examining this issue.</span></p></body></html>